An R0 of 1.0078 could best describe the data of Italy. Also, the curves of Wuhan could be appropriately simulated when R0 was assumed 1.0146 (Fig. 1d). Notably, the number of new hospital-admitted cases in Italy showed a decline in days 40–50 which could be attributed to the strict social distancing policies imposed by the government (Fig. 1c). To fit the model to the mortality data, parameter \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
