				\begin{document}$$K$$\end{document}K (Eq. 6) was set at 0.025 for Italy. Notably, when the same value was considered for Wuhan, the simulation curve was far higher than the reported official data (Fig. 1f). In agreement with this observation, the Chinese authorities have later declared the inaccuracy of the initial reports of deaths in Wuhan and boosted the number by 50%27.
